“The Prince I Became”- Ric Hassani’s years-in-the-making sophomore album, has arrived. Anchored by reflections on music success, betrayal, and growth, the project shows an expansion of the worldview and thought process of Ric Hassani since the breakout success of his debut album, “African Gentleman.” Read More: Stream: Ric Hassani Releases 17-Track Album “The Prince I Became” <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1350917 size-full lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/PHOTO-ASSET-1-scaled-e1614464975899.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1290" /> As evidenced by some of the music on “The Prince I Became”, Thunder Fire You especially, Ric has grown as a man and a lover. In this conversation with modern culture curator and communications expert, Victor Okpala on his Elevated Conversations series, Ric Hassani breaks down the journey between “African Gentleman” and “The Prince I Became” while sharing highlights from his life and newer information for the listening audience. Enjoy! 